name: Syncplicity
description: Add a Syncplicity Instance to connect your existing Syncplicity account to the	Cloud Storage & Documents Hub, allowing you to manage files, folders, users and their corresponding privileges. You will need your Syncplicity App Token or your Syncplicity account credentials to add an instance

configuration.name: Authentication Type
configuration.description: For OAuth2 authentication code grant type oauth2  select `oauth2`. For OAuth2 client credentials select `custom`

configuration.name: Syncplicity Company ID
configuration.description: The provisioning users Syncplicity company ID. This is used to send requests to all APIs requiring a company ID

configuration.name: Syncplicity API Subdomain
configuration.description: The api subdomain/region of the provisioning user

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Vendor Event Type
configuration.description: Vendor Event Type. Currently only polling is supported. Individual Syncpoints will be polled for file and folder events

configuration.name: Syncplicity User Email
configuration.description: The provisioning users email used to login to Syncplicity. This is used to send requests to determine proper API gateway

configuration.name: Access Token Lifetime
configuration.description: Lifetime of the Access Token in seconds

configuration.name: Event Syncpoint Details
configuration.description: The details of the syncpoints that are being polled in key:value format - syncpointId:lastVendorEventId

configuration.name: Event Poller Refresh Interval
configuration.description: How often to poll for events (in minutes). Defaults to 5

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses

configuration.name: Document Hub Tagging
configuration.description: Enable Tagging of Documents. Paths and Tags will be stored in CE database in Clear Text

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. For Syncplicity this is not editable and is managed internally by the connector

resources.description: Retrieves a specific file associated with an PATH. The file is directly streamed from the cloud storage provider through the connector, and is not buffered to disk. There is an optional Header `Offset` - The offset (in bytes) of the file data to download when download resume is needed. For example - if a file is 1000 bytes its range would be 0 to 999 so to get the second half of the file the offset would be set to `499`. When not provided the entire file will be downloaded
